  "texts": [
    "The octet can also decay into a singlet.",
    "However, we checked in [190] that the probability for that to happen during the lifetime of the fireball is negligible, so we ignore it, which is achieved in practice by taking p o m = 0 in eq.",
    "We note that in this model, the decay width of the bound state depends both on its binding energy and its wave function.In [191] we made a phenomenological application of this model.",
